<font size="4">\n[img[mother at tree]]\n\n//Guan-guan go the ospreys ,\nOn the islet in the river .\nThe modest , retiring , virtuous , young lady : --\nFor our prince a good mate she .//\n\n"Now, think carfeully," says your mother. "Which of these does not match the qualities you must have to find a good husband: humble, private, out-going, or moral?"\n\nAnswer your mother's Question <<textinput $poem [[Submit|Poem Answer]]>>\n</font><font size ="2">//*instructions: use all lowercase letters*//\n\n[[Unbind your feet and run away into the nearby woods|Run away]]\n</font>\n
<font size="4">\n[img[woods]]\n\nYou walk East until nightfall and then rest for the night. The following day you continue walking. At about noon you come to another split in the road.\n\n[[Take the road towards the North|North2]]\n[[Take the road towards the South|South1]]\n</font>

In that time you have found very little water to drink and nothing to eat. You sit down against a nearby tree to rest.\n\nIn a few minutes you hear movement on the road to the North. Squinting your eyes you see a caravan of merchants moving towards you with an escort of guards.\n\n[[Stand and approach the caravan|Enslavement]]\n[[Run into the woods and hide until the caravan passes|North3]]\n</font>

<font size="4">\n[img[woods night]]\n\nIt seems like you have been walking North forever. In reality it has been about a week. In that time you have found very little water to drink and nothing to eat. You sit down against a nearby tree to rest.\n\n[[Close your eyes to rest for a few minutes|Dehydration]]\n</font>

<font size="4">\n[img[mother inside scroll]]\n\nOuch!!! The pain of your foot binding is intense. You tell yourself that it is worth it, that keeping your feet small will attract a good husband. A wealthy man will consider your tiny feet a sign of obedience and good character. \n\nYour thoughts return to your mother who is finishing a lesson, "... and that is how we must see ourselves." Pointing to an unrolled scroll on the table, she commands,"Read this and then I will question you."\n\n[[Read the scroll| Scroll Text]]\n[[Remove your bindings and run away|Run away]]\n</font>
<font size="4">\n[img[mother at tree]]\n\nOuch!!! The pain from your foot binding startles you out of your daydream. It has been a week since your rejection by the county scholar. If you were a boy you would be on a path to a powerful position but instead you are standing by the old tree with your mother and sister, while the former recites a poem: \n\n//Guan-guan go the ospreys ,\nOn the islet in the river .\nThe modest , retiring , virtuous , young lady : --\nFor our prince a good mate she .//\n\nThe poem ends and your mother lectures, "In this ancient poem, young ladies are compared to an osprey because the osprey has the qualities that make a good wife. Which of these does not match the qualities you must have to find a good husband: humble, private, out-going, or moral?"\n\nAnswer your mother's Question <<textinput $poem [[Submit|Poem Answer]]>>\n</font><font size ="2">//*instructions: use all lowercase letters*//\n</font>
<<playsound "Temple Bell.mp3">>\n<font size="4">\n[img[a girl]]\n\nThe scholar's eyes snap open and his face looks like he just ate rotten fish, "A girl! You should know better than to come here, girls are not eligible for civil service positions. Go home and try to bring honor to your family some other way."\n\n[[Go home|Home]]\n</font>

<font size="4">\n[img[chinese scroll]]\n\nYou take the scroll and read...\n\n//On the third day after the birth of a girl the ancients observed three customs: first to place the baby below the bed; second to give her a piece of broken pottery; and third to give an offering to their ancestors.\n \nThese customs have three purposes: laying under the bed to show that the girl is lowly and must be humble, giving her pottery to teach her to work hard, and giving an offering to the ancestors to show that her primary duty is to make sure the family continues the ritual of ancestor worship.//\n\nAfter reading your mother asks, "What ritual is it the women's duty to continue in this family?"\n\nAnswer your mother's Question <<textinput $scroll [[Submit Answer|Scroll Answer]]>>\n</font><font size ="2">//*instructions: use all lowercase letters*//\n</font>

<font size="4">\n[img[guests 2]]\n\n//*Two Years Later*//\n\nOuch! The bindings aren't as painful as they used to be. Maybe your feet have stopped growing. Even so, you will need to bear with it today because your mother thinks you are ready to present to some guests. A wealthy bureaucrat from the city will arrive shortly and if you impress him you will be engaged to his son. This is a great opportunity for you and your family.\n\nAlready dressed in your best jacket and skirt, with your mother's most expensive makeup applied, you stand beside your mother in your family's tea room awaiting the guests. You hear them coming and your mother goes to the door to attend to them. As the guests enter you take a close look at the bureaucrat and his son. They have the same haughty and criticizing look that your mother always has. You immediately realize that a life with them will be just as hard as it has been with your mother. But you will be rich and important...\n\n[[Bow to the guests and greet thim with proper ritual| Engaged]]\n[[Remove your bindings and run away|Crippled]]\n</font>
<<playsound "Temple Bell.mp3">>\n<font size="4">\n[img[mother at tree closeup]]\n\n<<if $poem is "out-going">> "Your are correct," responds your mother but instead of praising you she sneers, "and I didn't think you were paying attention." She pauses then continues, "A good wife is humble, moral, and does not seek attention for herself but instead gains good attention for her husband and household." We will return home and continue our lessons tomorrow.\n\n[[Return home with your family|Ritual Practice]]\n<<else>> Your mother sighs, "That is wrong,". You need to pay attention if you wish to marry a good husband Now listen to the poem and try again..."\n\n[[Listen and try again|Poem Retry]]<<endif>>\n</font>

<font size="4">\n[img[master 1]]\n\nYou find master Xi sitting in the school garden at night. You are about to introduce yourself when he turns and says, " You must be the new student. I am master Xi, it is my responsibility to help students understand Tao (the Way).To begin your studies on this subject you must contemplate these words of the great master Confucius:\n\n"What Heaven gives us is called nature. Living in harmony with nature is called the Way. Learning the Way is called 'education.'"\n\nWould you like to see a painting that will help you understand these words better?\n\n[[Yes, I would like to see the painting|Painting of a poet on a mountain]]\n[[Go back to the courtyard]]\n</font>
<font size="4">\n[img[chinese scroll]]\n\n//On the third day after the birth of a girl the ancients observed three customs: first to place the baby below the bed; second to give her a piece of broken pottery; and third to give an offering to their ancestors.\n \nThese customs have three purposes: laying under the bed to show that the girl is lowly and must be humble, giving her pottery to teach her to work hard, and giving an offering to the ancestors to show that her primary duty is to make sure the family continues the ritual of ancestor worship.//\n\nYour mother questions you again "What ritual is it the women's duty to continue in this family??"\n\nAnswer your mother's Question <<textinput $scroll [[Submit|Scroll Answer]]>>\n[[Unbind your feet and run away into the nearby woods|Run away]]\n</font><font size ="2">//*instructions: use all lowercase letters*//\n</font>\n

<font size="4">\n<<loopsound "chinese_music.mp3">>\n[img[country home announcement]]\n\nIt is early morning when an official Ming messenger and two guards approach your family's farmhouse on horseback. The messenger disinterestedly calls to your family, "The time to recruit students for civil service is here. If anyone wishes to enter their county school they must be nominated by the county scholar. You can find the county scholar in his office in town."\n\nHis message given, the group trots off. You consider for a moment and decide that you definitely want to become an imperial scholar.\n\n[[Go and speak with the county scholar|County Scholar]]\n</font>

<font size="4">\n[img[county examiner]]\n\n"The final quesiton: who is the greatest master whose words teaches us to live in harmony and to follow the Tao?"\n\n<<textinput $ca3 [[Submit|County Answer 3]]>>\n</font><font size ="2">//*instructions: use all lowercase letters*//\n</font>\n
<font size="4">\n[img[poet on mountain]]\n\nMaster Xi unrolls a piece of paper and indicates for you to take a closer look. He describes the painting, "The man is a poet ascending a mountain. Below, in the trees, you can see his home. The artist of this painting uses the poet as a model for how we must live ."\n\nMaster Xi allows the noises of the night to surround you while you observe the painting. Finally he asks, "What word describes how the poet is living, is it apathy, domination, or harmony?\n\n<<textinput $harmony [[Submit|Harmony]]>>\n</font><font size ="2">//*instructions: use all lowercase letters*//\n</font>

<font size="4">\n[img[county school courtyard]]\n\nYou are back at the school courtyard. \n\n[[Find Master Xi to continue your studies on harmony|Master Xi]] \n[[Find Master Yangming to continue your studies on leadership|Master Yangming]] \n[[Approach the examiner to take the exam|Take the licensing exam]]\n</font>
<font size="4">\n[img[country home 1]]\n\nYou arrive home and see your father and mother holding a small bundle of bandages. As you approach you can see the anger in her eyes. “How dare you leave this house,” she yells as she hits you hard on the side of the head. “After all that we have invested in your future you decide to dishonor us by disappearing.” Holding the bandages out towards you she continues, “You will put your foot bindings back on immediately and return to your studies.”\n\n[[Go inside to bind your feet|Poem Lesson]]\n[[Run away into the nearby woods|Run away]]\n</font>
<font size="4">\n[img[county examiner]]\n\nThe official in green robes greets you, "Welcome to the county school, I am the county examiner. Here at this school we will prepare you for the Ming licensing exam, which you can take any time you feel ready. When you pass this exam you will receive the title Xiucai (flowering talent). This title will grant you admission to the provincial school located in town. However, before you attempt the exam, you should study with the master scholars that we have here. You may move about the school grounds and study at your own pace. Come back to me when you are ready for the exam."\n\n[[Find Master Xi to begin your studies on harmony|Master Xi]] \n[[Find Master Yangming to begin your studies on leadership|Master Yangming]] \n[[Take the exam without studying|Take the licensing exam]]\n</font>
<font size="4">\n[img[master2]]\n\nIn a dim room lit by flames you find one of the school masters. As you step forward the master speaks to you, "Greetings, I am master Yangming." Before you can say anything he continues, "I will attempt to teach you the true path of leadership. To gegin your education on this subject we must heed the words of the great master Confucius." Master Yangming closes his eyes and solemnly recites:\n\n<<print either("//A philosopher once asked Confucius what filial piety was. The Master said, 'It is not being disobedient.'//","//Confucius once said, 'If the son for three years does not alter from the way of his father, he has filial piety.'//","//Confucius once said, 'I can find no flaw in the character of Yu. He displays the utmost filial piety towards the spirits.'//")>>\n\nWould you like to hear a story that will help you understand leadership better?\n\n[[Yes, I would like to hear the story|Story of Shun the Great]]\n[[No, I would prefer to go back to the courtyard|Go back to the courtyard]]\n</font>

She pauses then continues, "A good wife is humble, moral, and does not seek attention for herself but instead gains good attention for her husband and household." Go to bed and we will continue tomorrow.\n\n[[Go to bed|guests]]\n<<else>> "Incorrect," barks your mother. "You ignorant, lazy girl! In that time you have found very little water to drink and nothing to eat. You sit down against a nearby tree to rest.\n\n[[Close your eyes to rest for a few minutes|Dehydration]]\n</font>

The advisors told the emperor that Shun's father and mother were cruel to him and that his brother was arrogant and lazy. Even in such a terrible family, Shun was a loyal son. He can always be seen working on his family's farm without a grudge, even though his family does not help.\n\nThe old emperor was so inspired by Shun's filial piety that he immidiately began training the boy to be emperor. When he decided that Shun was ready, the old emperor gave the throne to Shun and all of China enjoyed peace and happiness.//\n\nAfter finishing the story the master asks, "What quality did the boy possess that made him worthy to be emperor?"\n\n<<textinput $filial_piety [[Submit|Filial Piety]]>>\n</font><font size ="2">//*instructions: use all lowercase letters*//\n</font>

<font size="4">\n[img[woods night]]\n\nAfter the caravan passes you continue North. Over the course of the next few days very little changes, you have found very little water to drink and nothing to eat.
